AT ABOUT 4,000 FEET MSL, CPT ON SCH DOM FLIGHT REPORTED LOUD POP AND SUB 
SHUTDOWN OF RIGHT ENG. SMELL OF SMOKE AND VISUAL CONFIRMATION OF FIRE IN 
RIGHT NACELLE. SHIPS FIRE EXT ACTIVATED DURING RETURN TO DEPT. ARPT. LANDED 
WITHOUT FURTHER INCIDENT. INVESTIGATION REVLD FAILURE OF TURBINE 
STATOR RETAINING RING PANDW PART NO 3034363. PANDW HAD OUTSTANDING S.B. 
ISSUED AT THE TIME. THIS WAS ONLY ENG IN OPER FLIGHT THAT S.B. HAD NOT BEEN 
COMP ON. THIS ENG WAS ALSO LEAD ENG FOR OPER FLIGHT. 
